b'Wives and mothers waiting for their husbands and sons to return while trying to keep their family together.'
b'HHUGS step in to help emotionally, offer professional counselling, help with the mounting bills and try to restore the home and offer hope'
b'Children begin bed wetting, scared to sleep as they are constantly afraid another raid will happen and claim another family member.'
b'Children that are studying, during a raid their notes are taken, laptops. They have to stay strong for their family.'
b'They lose their breadwinner or their own jobs, suffer from depression, everything in life becomes blurry and they have no one to lean on.'
b'Those detained say "it is the family that suffers most" - as their family is left alone by the community and family.'
b'We have positively impacted many women and children since our inception. Our beneficiaries have referred to us as "helpers in Islam"'
b'HHUGS is the only charity of its kind in the world. We aim to relieve hardship, restore hope and rebuild lives for hundreds of individuals.'
